</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFC959BC16DE5757A" blockId="16.[831,1437,1862,2075]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFC959BC16D7C7AFC" bold="true" box="[831,1137,1925,1949]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was first described from Late Cretaceous of 
<collectingRegion id="8818F811FFFDFFBCFBB29BE16D5B7ADD" box="[1048,1110,1957,1980]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Texas</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="32CB7663FFFDFFBCFBC29BE16DB97ADC" box="[1128,1204,1957,1981]" name="United States of America" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">U.S.A.</collectingCountry>
). Also, it is recorded in the Esna Shale of northern Sinai (SAID &amp; KENAWY, 1956). In the study area, it is found in the Maastrichtian and Early-Middle Paleocene sediments.
</paragraph>
